# Git Conventions

## Commits (Conventional Commits)
Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`. Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `perf`, `security`. Suggested scopes: `api`, `auth`, `db`, `jobs`, `infra`, `ui`, `redis`, `nextjs`, `flask`. Breaking: `feat(api)!: ...`.

Examples: `feat(api): add patient search endpoint`, `fix(redis): prevent stale cache on update`, `test(nextjs): add login page integration tests`.

## Branches
`<type>/<issue>-<short-desc>` e.g. `feat/42-pathway-cloning`.

## Pull requests
Conventional title; body `Closes #N`; squash to `main`; CI green; 1+ reviewer for non-trivial work.

## Tooling
`.cz.toml` + Commitizen; `cz commit`; `CHANGELOG.md` on bump.
